ensg <- names(bwmod$colors)

## Function that returns the WC
makeWC <- function(i){
    i <- as.numeric(gsub("ME","",i))
    palNum <- sample(1:151,1)
    entre <- AnnotationDbi::select(org.Hs.eg.db, keytype="ENSEMBL", keys = ensg[bwmod$colors==i], columns = "ENTREZID")$ENTREZID
    wc <- wcGeneSummary(entre, max.words=200, random.order=FALSE,excludeFreq = 10000,
                        colors=pokepal(palNum),
                        rot.per=0.4)
    print(paste("Used palette:", palNum))
    wc$wc
}

## Use bnlearn
struc <- bwmod$MEs
struc$ME0 <- NULL
struc <- struc[rownames(struc)[stringr::str_starts(rownames(struc),"T")],]
bs <- boot.strength(struc, R=100, algorithm = "hc")
ave <- averaged.network(bs)

## Convert to igraph
g <- as.igraph(ave)

## Assign edge attributes
el <- data.frame(as_edgelist(g))
colnames(el) <- c("from","to")
el <- left_join(el, bs)
E(g)$strength <- el$strength
E(g)$direction <- el$direction

## Node attributes
pos <- layout_nicely(g)
V(g)$x <- pos[,1]
V(g)$y <- pos[,2]
V(g)$stripName <- gsub("ME","",V(g)$name)
sizes <- table(bwmod$colors)
V(g)$size <- as.numeric(sizes[V(g)$stripName])

## ggraph
gg <- ggraph(g, layout = "manual", x = x, y = y) + 
    theme_graph() +
    geom_edge_diagonal(position="identity",
                   angle_calc="along",
                   aes_(width=~I(strength),
                        edge_colour=~I(strength)),
                   arrow = arrow(length=unit(4, 'mm')),
                   end_cap=circle(4, 'mm')) +
    scale_edge_color_continuous(low="dodgerblue", high="tomato", name="strength")+
    scale_edge_width_continuous(range=c(1, 5), name="strength")+
    geom_node_point(aes(size=size), fill = "black", colour = "black", shape = 21)+
    scale_size(range=c(1,20))+
    geom_node_text(aes_(label=~stringr::str_wrap(name, width = 25)),
                   check_overlap=TRUE, repel=TRUE, size = 8,
                   color = "white",
                   bg.color = "black",
                   segment.color="black",
                   bg.r = .15)

## Return hub
hs <- hub.score(g, weights = E(g)$strength)
hs <- hs$vector[order(hs$vector, decreasing=TRUE)]

kable(hs, col.names="Score") %>%
  kable_classic(full_width = F, html_font = "Cambria") %>%
  scroll_box(width = "100%", height = "200px")
